README.md
     1‚Üí# NeverThrow üôÖ ‚Ä¶
     5‚Üí## Description
     7‚ÜíEncode failure into your program.
     8‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
    19‚Üí## Table Of Contents
    21‚Üí* [Installation](#installation)
    22‚Üí* [Recommended: Use `eslint-plugin-neverthrow`](#recommended-use-eslint-plugin-neverthrow)
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
    73‚Üí## Installation
    75‚Üí```sh
    76‚Üí> npm install neverthrow
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
    79‚Üí## Recommended: Use `eslint-plugin-neverthrow`
    81‚ÜíAs part of `neverthrow`s [bounty program](https://github.com/supermacro/neverthrow/issues/314), user [mdbetancourt](https://github.com/mdbetancourt) created [`eslint-plugin-neverthrow`](https://github.com/mdbetancourt/eslint-plugin-neverthrow) to ensure that errors are not gone unhandled.
    82‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   100‚Üí## Top-Level API
   102‚Üí`neverthrow` exposes the following:
   103‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   139‚Üí## API Documentation
   141‚Üí### Synchronous API (`Result`) ‚Ä¶
   143‚Üí#### `ok`
   145‚ÜíConstructs an `Ok` variant of `Result`
   146‚Üí
   147‚Üí**Signature:**
   148‚Üí
   149‚Üí```typescript
   150‚Üíok<T, E>(value: T): Ok<T, E> { ... }
   151‚Üí```
   152‚Üí
   153‚Üí**Example:**
   154‚Üí
   155‚Üí```typescript
   156‚Üíimport { ok } from 'neverthrow'
   157‚Üí
   158‚Üíconst myResult = ok({ myData: 'test' }) // instance of `Ok`
   159‚Üí
   160‚ÜímyResult.isOk() // true
   161‚ÜímyResult.isErr() // false
   162‚Üí```
   163‚Üí
   164‚Üí[‚¨ÜÔ∏è  Back to top](#toc)
   165‚Üí
   166‚Üí---
   167‚Üí
   863‚Üí### Asynchronous API (`ResultAsync`)
   865‚Üí#### `okAsync`
   867‚ÜíConstructs an `Ok` variant of `ResultAsync`
   868‚Üí
   869‚Üí**Signature:**
   870‚Üí
   871‚Üí```typescript
   872‚ÜíokAsync<T, E>(value: T): ResultAsync<T, E>
   873‚Üí```
   874‚Üí
   875‚Üí**Example:**
   876‚Üí
   877‚Üí```typescript
   878‚Üíimport { okAsync } from 'neverthrow'
   879‚Üí
   880‚Üíconst myResultAsync = okAsync({ myData: 'test' }) // instance of `ResultAsync`
   881‚Üí
   882‚Üíconst myResult = await myResultAsync // instance of `Ok`
   883‚Üí
   884‚ÜímyResult.isOk() // true
   885‚ÜímyResult.isErr() // false
   886‚Üí```
   887‚Üí
   888‚Üí[‚¨ÜÔ∏è  Back to top](#toc)
   889‚Üí
   890‚Üí---
   891‚Üí
  1519‚Üí### Utilities
  1521‚Üí#### `fromThrowable`
  1523‚ÜíTop level export of `Result.fromThrowable`.
  1524‚ÜíPlease find documentation at [Result.fromThrowable](#resultfromthrowable-static-class-method)
  1525‚Üí
  1526‚Üí[‚¨ÜÔ∏è  Back to top](#toc)
  1527‚Üí
  1633‚Üí### Testing
  1635‚Üí`Result` instances have two unsafe methods, aptly called `_unsafeUnwrap` and `_unsafeUnwrapErr` which **should only be used in a test environment**.
  1636‚Üí
  1637‚Üí`_unsafeUnwrap` takes a `Result<T, E>` and returns a `T` when the result is an `Ok`, otherwise it throws a custom object.
  1638‚Üí
  1639‚Üí`_unsafeUnwrapErr` takes a `Result<T, E>` and returns a `E` when the result is an `Err`, otherwise it throws a custom object.
  1640‚Üí
  1641‚ÜíThat way you can do something like:
  1642‚Üí
  1643‚Üí```typescript
  1644‚Üíexpect(myResult._unsafeUnwrap()).toBe(someExpectation)
  1645‚Üí```
  1646‚Üí
  1647‚ÜíHowever, do note that `Result` instances are comparable. So you don't necessarily need to unwrap them in order to assert expectations in your tests. So you could also do something like this:
  1648‚Üí
  1649‚Üí```typescript
  1650‚Üíimport { ok } from 'neverthrow'
  1651‚Üí
  1652‚Üí// ...
  1653‚Üí
  1654‚Üíexpect(callSomeFunctionThatReturnsAResult("with", "some", "args")).toEqual(ok(someExpectation));
  1655‚Üí```
  1656‚Üí
  1657‚ÜíBy default, the thrown value does not contain a stack trace. This is because stack trace generation [makes error messages in Jest harder to understand](https://github.com/supermacro/neverthrow/pull/215). If you want stack traces to be generated, call `_unsafeUnwrap` and / or `_unsafeUnwrapErr` with a config object:
  1658‚Üí
  1659‚Üí```typescript
  1660‚Üí_unsafeUnwrapErr({
  1661‚Üí  withStackTrace: true,
  1662‚Üí})
  1663‚Üí
  1664‚Üí// ^ Now the error object will have a `.stack` property containing the current stack
  1665‚Üí```
  1666‚Üí
  1667‚Üí---
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
  1673‚Üí## A note on the Package Name
  1675‚ÜíAlthough the package is called `neverthrow`, please don't take this literally. I am simply encouraging the developer to think a bit more about the ergonomics and usage of whatever software they are writing.
  1676‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
  1681‚Üí### License
  1683‚ÜíThe neverthrow project is available as open source under the terms of the [MIT license](https://github.com/supermacro/neverthrow/blob/master/LICENSE).
